Calvin Harris has been announced as a performer at the MTV EMAs in Glasgow next month. Calvin Harris to perform at the Glasgow MTV EMAs Calvin Harris has been announced as a performer at the MTV EMAs in Glasgow next month.The Scottish DJ will perform at the award show for the first time at the SSE Hydro in Glasgow on Sunday, November 9.He will join a whole host of other performers including Kiesza, Charli XCX, Royal Blood, Ariana Grande, Ozzy Osbourne and Ed Sheeran.Rapper Nicki Minaj will host the event.Calvin played at Glasgow's BBC Radio 1 Big Weekend earlier this year, and he made his Hydro debut last December when his tour with Tiesto took over the venue.He is due to release new album Motion on November 4. 